---
// Hero: big typographic intro. Text is placeholder — user to refine.
---

<section class="px-6 pt-20 pb-24 sm:px-10 sm:pt-28 sm:pb-32">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <h1
      class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-5xl leading-[1.05] tracking-tight sm:text-7xl"
    >
      Hi, I'm <em class="text-[color:var(--color-accent)]">Dragosh</em> — a
      programmer with a strong focus on games.
    </h1>
    <p
      class="mt-8 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-muted)] sm:text-xl"
    >
      Final-year Computer Science student at
      <span class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam</span>.
      I work with <span class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">Godot</span> and
      <span class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">C++</span>, currently prototyping
      a small game built around real-time liquid physics. On the side I'm practicing
      shader programming and making my own pixel art in Aseprite. Looking for a first
      role as a software engineer — ideally in game development, at a studio large
      or small, but open to broader tech roles.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-sm">
      <a
        href="#contact"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-[color:var(--color-ink)] px-5 py-2.5 text-[color:var(--color-paper)] transition hover:opacity-90"
      >
        Get in touch <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
      </a>
      <a
        href="#projects"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-[color:var(--color-rule)] px-5 py-2.5 transition hover:border-[color:var(--color-ink)]"
      >
        See projects
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
